{
  "message": "chore: update RaptorQ wavefront benchmark artifact with fresh timing data\n\nRefresh the F6 wavefront pipeline benchmark numbers from a recent run.\nThe file is gitignored but has been tracked since the initial wavefront\npipeline feature landed (42e2b6f2). Key changes in the new measurements:\n\n- Sequential baseline p50 dropped from ~40763 to ~40069 \u00b5s (slight\n  improvement likely from recent runtime fixes)\n- Wavefront batch_size=4 now shows +7.5% delta vs sequential (was -0.4%)\n  indicating the wavefront overhead is more visible at small batch sizes\n  on this hardware\n- Wavefront batch_size=16 is now essentially neutral (+0.07%) vs the\n  previous -1.7%, consistent with the expected crossover point\n\nThese are benchmark artifacts, not behavioral changes. The shifts are\nwithin normal variance for microbenchmarks on shared hardware.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
